California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
If you are a California
resident
,
you have specific rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). These rights include:
l
Right to Know:
You have the right to request that we disclose to you
: (1) the categories and/or specific pieces of personal information they have collected about you, (2) the categories of sources for that personal information, (3) the purposes for which we use that information, (4) the categories of third parties with whom we disclose or share the information, and (5) the categories of information that we sell, share or disclose to third parties.
l
Right to Delete:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information that we have collected, subject to certain exceptions.
l
Right to Opt-Out
of Sale or Sharing
:
You have the right to request that we stop selling or sharing your personal information (
"
opt-out
"
) .
Note that the CCPA defines
"
sell
"
and
"
personal information
"
very broadly, and some of our data sharing described in this Privacy Policy may be considered a
"
