GDPR Rights for EU Residents
If you are a resident of the European Union (EU), you have
the following rights under
the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):
l
Right to be Informed:
You have to the right to be informed about the collection and use of your personal data.
l
Right to Access:
You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you and to obtain a copy of that
data
.
l
Right to Rectification:
You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate or incomplete
.
l
Right to Erasure:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal
data
when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, or if you withdraw your consent on which the processing is based.
l
Right to Restrict Processing:
You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal
data
under certain circumstances, such as when you contest the accuracy of the
data
or when you object to the processing.
l
Right to Data Portability:
You have the right to receive your personal
data
in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format and to transmit that
data
to another data controller.
l
Right to Object:
You have the right to object to the processing of your personal
data
on grounds related to your particular situation, including processing for direct marketing purposes.
l
Rights
in Relation to
Automated Decision-Making:
You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produce legal effects concerning you or similarly significantly affect you.
l
Right to Complain:
You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority about our collection and use of your personal data. For more information, please contact your local supervisory authority. Certain supervisory authorities require that you exhaust our own internal complaints process before looking into your complaint.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
ginrummy.contact@gmail.com
. We will respond to your request in accordance with the GDPR requirements.
