Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data
We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:
1.
Consent:
We may process your personal data if you have given us explicit consent to do so for a specific purpose. You have the right to withdraw your consent at any time.
2.
Contractual Necessity:
We may process your personal data when it is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party or to take steps at your request prior to entering into a contract.
3.
Legal Obligation:
We may process your personal data if we need to comply with a legal obligation to which we are subject.
4.
Legitimate Interests:
We may process your personal data when it is necessary for our legitimate interests or the legitimate interests of a third party, provided that your interests and fundamental rights do not override those interests.
5.
Public Interest:
In some cases, we may process your personal data in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in us.
